    <title>Of forgotten condoms. And days without pants.</title>
    <link>https://www.scarleteen.com/blog/heather_corinna/2013/01/22/of_forgotten_condoms_and_days_without_pants</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;It occurs to me that the &quot;we both forgot to use condoms&quot; thing that comes up often enough is a bit like suggesting that a person forgot to wear pants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a whole day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And didn&#039;t notice.&lt;/p&gt;
